bmitted-evidence-06-defendant-26011b5f6d79.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","relevance":"Official source on Operation Absolute Resolve showing both adverse facts (Caracas operation and transition comments) and defense facts (capture/extraction, criminal proceedings, joint military/law-enforcement mission, no U.S. casualties, anti-narcoterrorism context).","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T00:29:30Z","sha256":"26011b5f6d792bc39d1eabe168123482dcc270e34745035055127683c27c55e1","size_bytes":2203,"source_description":"Department of War/Pentagon News article by Matthew Olay, opened via web.open on 2026-06-30.","source_url":"https://www.war.gov/News/News-Stories/Article/Article/4370431/trump-announces-us-militarys-capture-of-maduro/","storage_name":"26/26011b5f6d792bc39d1eabe168123482dcc270e34745035055127683c27c55e1","submitted_by_role":"defendant","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"DX-1 Department of War article on Maduro capture as joint law-enforcement mission"},{"admissibility_status":"submitted_evidence","created_at":"2026-06-30T00:21:36Z","evidence_id":"ev_2efdab998e47_submitted-evidence-03-plaintiff-2efdab998e47","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"submitted-evidence-03-plaintiff-2efdab998e47.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","relevance":"Contemporaneous credible reporting on the U.S. buildup, strikes, first known operation on Venezuelan soil, Jan. 3 large-scale strike across Caracas, capture/removal of Maduro and Flores, and related military posture.","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T00:21:00Z","sha256":"2efdab998e47ae16cff6d6becb03e7e9216bee4b668814addd1ef89d84c57ec8","size_bytes":2038,"source_description":"PBS NewsHour page carrying Associated Press timeline by Ben Finley, Konstantin Toropin, and Regina Garcia Cano; extracted via web.open/find on 2026-06-30.","source_url":"https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/a-timeline-of-u-s-military-escalation-against-venezuela-leading-to-maduros-capture","storage_name":"2e/2efdab99