tor General report to Congress on Operation Southern Spear, January 1-March 31 2026, opened via web.open PDF extraction on 2026-06-30.","source_url":"https://media.defense.gov/2026/May/21/2003935694/-1/-1/1/OSS_Q2_MAR2026_FINAL_508.PDF","storage_name":"53/53782f10ceb9c41feb405f741ad20b53fef01f5306f2442df751c9f7a09e5345","submitted_by_role":"defendant","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"DX-2 Lead IG Operation Southern Spear report extract on counter-narcotics mission"},{"admissibility_status":"submitted_evidence","created_at":"2026-06-30T00:21:17Z","evidence_id":"ev_6627f15cd3a4_submitted-evidence-02-plaintiff-6627f15cd3a4","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"submitted-evidence-02-plaintiff-6627f15cd3a4.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","relevance":"Official U.S. statements acknowledging two-hour U.S. ground presence in Venezuela, oil quarantine/pressure, retained options, and the adverse claim that the action was not an invasion.","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T00:20:30Z","sha256":"6627f15cd3a42cc9018d2ab70f1951aa4f1687bd18848c031287516048d42d80","size_bytes":1793,"source_description":"White House release page, extracted via web.open on 2026-06-30.","source_url":"https://www.whitehouse.gov/releases/2026/01/rubio-this-is-our-hemisphere-and-president-trump-will-not-allow-our-security-to-be-threatened/","storage_name":"66/6627f15cd3a42cc9018d2ab70f1951aa4f1687bd18848c031287516048d42d80","submitted_by_role":"plaintiff","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"PX-2 White House release collecting Secretary Rubio statements"},{"admissibility_status":"submitted_evidence","created_at":"2026-06-30T00:22:10Z","evidence_id":"ev_94e861ebadbf_submitted-evidence-05-plaintiff-94e861ebadbf","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"submitted-evidence-05-plaintiff-94e861ebadbf.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","relevance":"Independent international-law analysis characterizing the operation as U.S. forces operating in Venezuela, strikes around Caracas, special-forces abduction, and a U.S. announcement to run/administer a transition under threat of force.","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T00:22:00Z","sha256":"94e861ebadbf2849cd4257d954fcd51afc5f6a8d01c7b5f2df165cc6d4180151","size_bytes":1755,"source_description":"Chatham House expert comment by Marc Weller, extracted via web.open/find on 2026-06-30.","source_url":"https://www.chathamhouse.org/2026/01/us-capture-president-nicolas-maduro-and-attacks-venezuela-have-no-justification","storage_name":"94/94e861ebadbf2849cd4257d954fcd51afc5f6a8d01c7b5f2df165cc6d4180151","submitted_by_role":"plaintiff","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"PX-5 Chatham House analysis of U.S. capture, strikes, and transition control"}]},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":false,"deadline":"2026-06-30T00:48:10.359530297Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C2","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C2","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":877700,"role_id":"council","turn_number":10}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"list_evidence"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782779612661},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my careful review of the admitted record, I have analyzed the key evidence:\n\n**Critical Findings:**\n\n1. **Official U.S. Sources (DX-1, PX-1, PX-2):**\n   - Operation Absolute Resolve involved a joint military/law-enforcement mission in Caracas against a heavily fortified military fortress\n   - U.S. forces were on Venezuelan ground for about two hours to capture Maduro\n   - The operation is consistently described as \"capture,\" \"extraction,\" and \"to bring Maduro to justice\"\n   - Official statements explicitly say it was \"not an invasion\" and \"not an extended military operation\"\n\n2. **Contemporaneous Reporting (PX-3):**\n   - Confirms late-December operation on Venezuelan soil and January 3 large-scale strike across Caracas\n   - Documents the massive military buildup, strikes on boats, and the capture/removal of Maduro\n\n3. **Expert Analysis (PX-4, PX-5):**\n   - Brookings preserves the official position that it was \"not an invasion\" and \"we did not occupy a country\"\n   - Chatham House characterizes it as a significant sovereignty violation and describes Trump's announcement that the U.S. would \"run Venezuela and administer a political transition\"\n\n4. **The Decisive Issue:**\n   The proposition requires a military offensive **intended to establish control over any portion of Venezuelan territory**. The credible-source consensus shows:\n   - U.S. forces did temporarily control a target area in Caracas during the raid\n   - However, the official framing consistently describes the operational objective as capture/extraction, not territorial control\n   - The transition language about \"overseeing Venezuela\" refers to political leverage, not territorial administration\n   - No evidence shows U.S. forces remained to hold, govern, or administer any Venezuelan territory after the two-hour operation\n\n**Conclusion:**\nUnder the preponderance standard, the admitted record does not prove the specific intent to establish territorial control. The stronger evidence shows the operational object was capture and extraction, with temporary tactical control serving that purpose rather than a plan to possess or administer Venezuelan land.\n\nTherefore, I find the proposition **not demonstrated**."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"EDfTweru0","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The record proves a serious U.S. military raid inside Caracas but official sources and credible reporting consistently frame the operational objective as capture/extraction, not territorial control; the decisive intent element remains unproved under a preponderance standard.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"mistralai/mistral-medium-3-5","usage":{"input":3431,"output":545,"cacheRead":40224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44200,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782779612663,"responseId":"gen-1782779612-A65mphVo3MKIaxeTsYOw","responseModel":"mistralai/mistral-medium-3.5-20260430"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"EDfTweru0","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C2\ncase_id: arb-ex05-20260630001330\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C2\nremaining_ms: 872284\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex05-20260630001330\",\"member_id\":\"C2\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T00:48:10.359530297Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C2\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C2\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":872284,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":10}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C2\ncase_id: arb-ex05-20260630001330\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C2\nremaining_ms: 872284\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex05-20260630001330\",\"member_id\":\"C2\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T00:48:10.359530297Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C2\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C2\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":872284,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":10}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex05-20260630001330","member_id":"C2","ok":true,"result":{"text":"Council vote accepted."},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":true,"deadline":"2026-06-30T00:48:10.359530297Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C2","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C2","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":872284,"role_id":"council","turn_number":10}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"submit_council_vote"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782779618076},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"My vote was accepted. The proposition was found **not demonstrated** because, while the record proves a serious U.S. military raid inside Caracas with temporary tactical control, the official sources and credible reporting consistently frame the operational objective as capture/extraction rather than an intent to establish territorial control over any portion of Venezuela."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"mistralai/mistral-medium-3-5","usage":{"input":799,"output":64,"cacheRead":43632,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44495,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782779618077,"responseId":"gen-1782779618-AsPTndJvTvbwbDtWE8f2","responseModel":"mistralai/mistral-medium-3.5-20260430"}],"willRetry":false}
